{{Infobox company | name = Visual China Group | logo = Visual China Group logo.png | type = [[Public company|Public]] | traded_as = {{szse|000681}} | industry = [[Stock photos]] | location = [[Beijing]], [[China]] | founded = 2000 | subsid = [[500px]] | website = {{url|https://www.vcg.com/}} }} '''Visual China Group''' (also known as '''VCG''') is a Beijing, China-based [[stock photo|photo]] and media agency. Established in 2000, it is a supplier of stock multimedia content to the commercial media industry. VCG is currently the largest stock image and media footage provider in China and third largest in the world.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dpreview.com/news/6061266792/500px-acquired-by-chinese-licensing-giant-visual-china-group|title=500px acquired by Chinese licensing giant Visual China Group|work=DPReview|access-date=2018-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160122005714/en/Getty-Images-Visual-China-Group-Partner-Exclusive|title=Getty Images and Visual China Group Partner in Exclusive Global Distribution Partnership for Extensive Visual Content Collection of Corbis Images|access-date=2018-07-15|language=en}}</ref> The company is often dubbed as "The [[Getty Images|Getty]] of China".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.diyphotography.net/500px-sold-visual-china-group-getty-china/|title=500px sold to Visual China Group, the "Getty of China" - DIY Photography|date=2018-02-26|work=DIY Photography|access-date=2018-07-15|language=en-US}}</ref>
Since 2006, VCG has served as the exclusive distributor of [[Getty Images]]' library in China. In January 2016, Unity Glory International, an affiliate of VCG, announced that it would acquire the image licensing business of [[Branded Entertainment Network|Corbis]]. Unity Glory will license the Corbis libraries to Getty for distribution outside of China via VCG.<ref name="variety-corbissold">{{cite web|title=Bill Gates’ Corbis Images Sold to Visual China Group|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/asia/bill-gates-corbis-images-sold-to-visual-china-1201687743/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=26 January 2016|first=Patrick|last=Frater|date=January 25, 2016}}</ref><ref name="time-imagewar">{{cite news|title=The Decade-Long Image Licensing War Is Suddenly Over|url=http://time.com/4190784/image-licensing-war-is-over/|accessdate=26 January 2016|website=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|first=Olivier|last=Laurent|date=January 22, 2016}}</ref> In early 2018, it acquired photo sharing website [[500px]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/02/26/one-time-flickr-rival-500px-acquired-by-the-getty-of-china-vcg/|title=One-time Flickr rival 500px acquired by the Getty of China, VCG|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2018-07-15|language=en-US}}</ref>
